root_cause: Agent sandbox blocks deepchem/pickle imports during development, causing pipreqs to not detect these packages, which means DGL is not installed for CGCNN model
fix_description: instruction_override tells agent to include proper import statements for CGCNNModel; this triggers pipreqs detection and DGL post-install hook
notes: Docker base image has Python 3.10, TensorFlow 2.17 pre-installed. CGCNN requires DGL which is only installed if deepchem is detected by pipreqs.
